# TB Pro Theme Ticket Expansions

**Every theme visualization row** must be expandable to ticket IDs — no exceptions.

Applies to: long-close themes, Flight 2 themes, all-launch leaderboard, misdirected, any `.theme-row` block.

## Ticket line format — PII-redacted subject, not theme paraphrase

Each ticket line: **`#ID` link + PII-redacted subject** — never theme-name paraphrase, never ID-only.

**Repo rule:** PII must never exist in any repo file — committed or local. Always run subjects through `_redact()` / `pii_redact.redact()` before writing HTML or markdown into this repo.

Lisa confirmed: subjects are useful for knowing what to click. Generic labels (e.g. "Request or complaint") lose too much signal.

- **Subject display:** show the actual Zendesk subject with PII stripped via `_redact()` — emails → `[email]`, IPs → `[IP]`.
- **Fallback:** if subject is blank after redaction, fall back to `classify_ticket(t)` theme name.
- **Non-English:** append `*(Non-English)*` when subject contains non-ASCII characters.
- **`.eng-card__subject`:** same rule — redacted subject, not a generic label.

**Generator:** `_redact()` and `_ticket_li()` in `tbpro_launch_overview.py` handle this — do not bypass them.

**Footer:** *"Ticket subjects shown with PII redacted; non-English quotes include AI translations."*

## Required HTML pattern

Wrap each theme in `.theme-row-wrap`. The bar/count row stays in `.theme-row`; ticket list goes in `<details class="theme-tickets">`:

```html
<div class="theme-row-wrap">
  <div class="theme-row">…name, count, bar…</div>
  <details class="theme-tickets">
    <summary>N tickets</summary>
    <ul class="theme-tickets__list">
      <li>
        <a href="https://tbpro.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/{id}" target="_blank">#{id}</a>
        <span class="theme-tickets__subj"> — Redacted subject text</span>
        <span class="theme-tickets__gh"><a href="…">repo#issue</a></span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </details>
</div>
```

- Link format: `https://tbpro.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/{id}`
- Summary count must match list length (`summary` text ↔ `<li>` count).

## Data source & common mistakes

Re-fetch Zendesk (`fetch_tickets()` / `_ticket_li()` in `tbpro_launch_overview.py`; `zd_search_all()` in `tbpro_daily.py`) before embedding lists. Do not hardcode stale IDs or paste raw subjects.

Reference: `lisa/daily/launch_overview_sample.html`.
